Description: Part of a calcite vessel: comprising three joined fragments, bearing the incised names on the exterior surface. Good condition.
Curator's comments: Petrie, in Royal Tombs of the Earliest Dynasties' I, 19, says of this fragment, 'It was usurped by Azab, and is the only piece of his that we found in his tomb.' But the object itself bears the excavation mark 'Z', indicating the tomb of Djet, which is presumably an error. Bibliography: W. M. F. Petrie, 'Royal Tombs of the Earliest Dynasties' I, pl. V, 11; note that the references in B. Porter & R. Moss, 'Topographical Bibliography of Ancient Egyptian Hieroglyphic Texts, Reliefs and Paintings' V (Oxford: Clarendon Press), 84-5 do not refer to this piece but to 1910,1008.1.
